# Layered architecture

Allowed flow: **`apps/web` → `packages/application` → `packages/domain`**; **`packages/infrastructure` → `packages/domain`**; application orchestrates domain + ports.

| Layer | Folder | Rule |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Domain | `packages/domain` | Pure: no React, `fetch`, `localStorage`, or browser APIs. Aggregates and services (Build, PassiveSpec, Item, calc…). |
| Application | `packages/application` | Use cases; depends on **domain** (and contracts); not on UI components. |
| Infrastructure | `packages/infrastructure` | Port implementations (HTTP loaders, storage, XML, trade via BFF when it exists). |
| Web app | `apps/web` | Thin SPA: routes, composition, shadcn, Query; **no** PoB business rules inside components. |

Respect `scope:*` tags and `@nx/enforce-module-boundaries` in `eslint.config.mjs`. Do not bypass with relative imports that violate boundaries.
